div.p:
If yea;
Answ. then they may joyne together into a Church, without any succession, or dependency, on other Churches; if not, either they must require some superstitious
or prophane Minister, to receive in Members, Ordaine Officers, in a true Church, which is absurd: or else they must stay, till they meet with another true Church and Ministery, which, besides the difficulty, savoreth of a Prelaticall Jurisdiction of one Church over another; of which, something anon.
